o navigation search for other people with the same name see jim corbett disambiguation this article needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed march  learn how and when to remove this template message james j corbett statistics real name james john corbett nicknames gentleman jim weights heavyweight height  ft  in  m reach  in  cm nationality american born september   san francisco california us died february   aged  bayside queens new york city us stance orthodox boxing record total fights  wins  wins by ko  losses  draws  no contests  james john gentleman jim corbett september   – february   was an american professional boxer and a former world heavyweight champion best known as the man who defeated the great john l sullivan despite a career spanning only  bouts corbett faced the best competition his era had to offer squaring off with a total of  fighters who would later be enshrined alongside him in the international boxing hall of fame contents  biography  boxing career  professional boxing record  life after boxing  films  see also  references  external links biographyedit in  jims father patrick corbett had emigrated from ballycusheen ballinrobe county mayo ireland to the us james corbett returned to ballinrobe in  and among the highlights of his visit were the boxing demonstrations he gave in ballinrobe town hall the proceeds from the events entrance fees were donated for the upkeep of partry church where his uncle the reverend james corbett was then parish priest he also donated a stained glass window to the church he also coached boxing at the olympic club in san francisco he stood at  ft  in  m with a reach of  inches  cm boxing careeredit this section does not cite any sources please help improve this section by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed april  learn how and when to remove this template message dubbed by the media as gentleman jim corbett he graduated from sacred heart high school in san francisco and was rumored to have a college education he also pursued a career in acting performing at a variety of theatres he has been called the father of modern boxing for his scientific approach and innovations in techniquecitation needed  corbett vs jackson on may   corbett fought peter black prince jackson a muchheralded bout between crosstown rivals since corbett and jackson were boxing instructors at san franciscos two most prestigious athletic clubs they fought to a nocontest after  rounds the fight vaulted corbett to even greater national prominence and the public clamored for a contest between sullivan and him the champion reluctantly agreed and the fight was finally set corbett went into rigorous training and was even more confident of his chances after he sparred with sullivan in a short exhibition match on a san francisco stage on september   at the olympic club in new orleans louisiana corbett won the world heavyweight championship by knocking out john l sullivan in the st round corbetts new scientific boxing technique enabled him to dodge sullivans rushing attacks and wear him down with jabs corbett did not prove to be a fighting champion in todays terms meaning he defended the title very rarely what must be remembered is this was an era before boxing commissions and the regulation of the sport was minimal at best boxing was outlawed in most states so arranging a time and place for a bout was largely a hitandmiss proposition corbett treasured his title and viewed it as the ultimate promotional tool for his two main sources of income theatrical performances and boxing exhibitions play media the  boxing match vs peter courtney the  boxing match vs fitzsimmons in his only successful title defense on january   corbett knocked out charley mitchell of great britain in three rounds on september   he took part in the production of one of the first recorded boxing events a fight with peter courtney this was filmed at the black maria studio at west orange new jersey and was produced by william kl dickson it was only the second boxing match to be recorded jim corbett lost his heavyweight championship to the cornish british boxer bob fitzsimmons in carson city nevada corbett was dominant for most of the fight and knocked fitzsimmons to the canvas in the sixth round fitzsimmons recovered and though badly cut rallied from that point on when mrs fitzsimmons called out hit him in the slats bob where slats meant the abdominal area her husband followed her advice the body blows took their toll and though corbett continued to outbox his opponent masterfully ringsiders could see the champion slowing down fitzsimmons put corbett down in the th round with a withering body blow to the solar plexus and corbett despite his best efforts to do so could not regain his feet by the end of the tencount this fight lasting over an hour and a half was released to cinemas later that year as the corbettfitzsimmons fight the longest film ever released at the time devastated by the loss of his title corbett did everything he could to lure fitzsimmons back into the ring he was sure fitzsimmonss victory had been a fluke mostly attributed to his overtraining which left him short on stamina in the later rounds and was confident he would win the rematch perhaps fitzsimmons felt the same way for not even a  guaranteed purse posted by corbetts manager william a brady could get ruby robert back into the ring with gentleman jim it may also have been fitzsimmons intense personal dislike of corbett who had often publicly insulted him which ruled out any chance of another fight corbett training for his fight with jeffries this set the stage for what most boxing experts and ring historians consider to be corbetts finest fight refusing to face corbett ruby robert chose the hulking james j jeffries a former sparring partner of corbetts and a big heavyweight even by modern standards for his title defense fitzsimmons did some damage in the early rounds but jeffries weathered the storm and took the title in the th round jeffries had learned much of his trade training with corbett and was now handled by corbetts old manager william brady corbett who had been put on the back burner during fitzsimmons reign wasted no time in suggesting a title fight between his old sparring partner and himself brady liking corbett and reflecting after a recent poor showing against tom sharkey that his old fighter had little left in the tank at  agreed to the match the fight was set for the seaside arena in coney island new york while jeffries went through the motions in training corbett prepared like a spartan for battle he knew with his speed he could box rings around his larger and stronger opponent but he was giving up size strength almost  lb in weight and a sevenyear age difference the key was stamina and the ability to last the round fight limit the early rounds saw corbett moving quickly while big jeff attempted body shots however jeffries could not lay a glove on the dancing master round after round corbett had his way darting in to land punches then dancing away to avoid retaliation by the th round jeffries corner was in a panic manager brady dismissed trainer tommy ryan from the corner and took charge himself with the simple but direct order knock him out or lose your title corbett only had to stay upright for the last five rounds to be heavyweight champion once again jeffries stalked corbett around the ring looking for an opening corbett danced away from any threat through the nd round midway through the rd round corbett leaned back to avoid a jeffries blow bounced off the ropes and was put on the canvas by a short right hand he was counted out corbett found himself embraced by the public after this gallant effort the adoration was shortlived as his next fight a fiveround knockout over kid mccoy was widely believed to be a fix corbett managed to contest for the heavyweight title one last time when he met jeffries for a second match in san francisco in  now  reflexes slowing corbett survived a withering body blow in the second round and used every trick he knew to hang on until being knocked out in the tenth professional boxing recordedit  wins  knockouts  defeats  knockouts  draws  no contests res record opponent type rd time date location notes loss  james j jeffries tko    mechanics pavilion san francisco california for world heavyweight title win  kid mccoy ko    madison square garden new york new york loss  james j jeffries ko     seaside ac coney island new york for world heavyweight title loss  tom sharkey dq    lenox ac new york new york loss  bob fitzsimmons ko   the race track arena carson city nevada lost world heavyweight title draw  tom sharkey pts    mechanics pavilion san francisco california win  charley mitchell ko   duvall athletic club jacksonville florida retained world heavyweight title win  john l sullivan ko    olympic club new orleans louisiana won world heavyweight title win  ed kinney pts   milwaukee wisconsin nc  peter jackson nc   california ac san francisco california win  dominick mccaffrey tko    fifth avenue casino brooklyn new york win  jake kilrain pts   southern ac new orleans louisiana draw  dave campbell pts   mechanics pavilion portland oregon win  australian billy smith pts   portland oregon win  australian billy smith pts   portland oregon win  joe choynski ko   benicia harbor california nc  joe choynski nc   fairfax california win  william miller pts   san francisco california draw  duncan mcdonald pts   opera house salt lake city utah win  frank smith dq   pavilion salt lake city utah life after boxingedit james j corbett applying acting makeup following his retirement from boxing corbett returned to acting appearing in lowbudget films and giving talks about pugilism he also performed a minstrel show in blackface in skits with cornelius j obrien he authored his autobiography under the title the roar of the crowd the story was serialized by the saturday evening post in six weekly installments during octobernovember  the following year gp putnams sons published it in book form marketing it as the true tale of the rise and fall of a champion in  the story was made into a hollywood motion picture titled gentleman jim starring errol flynn as corbett from  until his death corbett lived at  corbett road in a threestory home in the bayside neighborhood of the borough of queens in new york city in  he had a friendly sparring match with the future champion gene tunney an admirer of corbetts scientific style tunney was amazed at the ability of corbett to spar even at the age of about  even claiming corbett had better defense than benny leonard on his passing in  corbett was interred in the cypress hills cemetery in brooklyn new york on its creation he was elected posthumously to the international boxing hall of fame corbetts brother joe corbett was a major league baseball pitcher corbett was married to mary olive morris higgins from  to  after their divorce he married the actress jessie taylor also known by her stage name vera she survived corbett by more than a quarter century living in their home at  corbett road in bayside new york corbetts greatgreatgreatnephew dan corbett was a professional heavyweight boxer from san antonio texas who won the united states boxing federation and international boxing organization intercontinental heavyweight titles before retiring in  the actor james davidson played corbett in the episode the fight san francisco never forgot of the syndicated western television series death valley days hosted by ronald w reagan in the story line walter watson john mcliam becomes boxing instructor at the olympic club in san francisco in this capacity he fights off a local bully and begins training corbett to face him in a match vital to the future of watson and the club corbett had a record of  wins with  by knockout  losses  draws  no contests and  no decisions newspaper decisions  filmsedit advertising for the midnight man  i remember jim corbett very well for he was a very important part of the first motion picture that we made for public exhibition thomas edison wrote in a letter from  yes he can justly claim the distinction of being the oldest living film star and i extend him my heart congratulations corbett and courtney before the kinetograph  actors fund field day  how championships are won—and lost  the man from the golden west  the burglar and the lady  based on the play of the same name that he also appeared in the other girl  the midnight man  the prince of avenue a  the beauty shop  james j corbett and neil obrien  happy days  at the round table  see alsoedit list of heavyweight boxing champions list of lineal boxing world champions list of lefthanded boxers referencesedit  county mayo mayoie retrieved march     james j corbetts professional boxing record boxreccom retrieved on september    neil obrien dies at  retired minstrel once with primrose and dockstader new york times january   retrieved february   mr obrien then joined james j corbett the boxing champion in presenting a comedy vaudeville act    nagler barney september   gentleman in the house on corbett road the new york times retrieved december     rather john a high quality of life within the city the new york times august   accessed october   james j gentleman jim corbett the heavyweight boxing champion from  to  lived from  to  in a large threestory home on a street that bears his name  the fight san francisco never forgot on death valley days internet movie data base march   retrieved september     corbett james j weir hugh december  the first film star tells his own story the new movie jamaica new york tower magazines inc retrieved november     james j corbett film  movie information citwfcom retrieved march    external linksedit wikimedia commons has media related to james j co