did some damage in the early rounds but jeffries weathered the storm and took the title in the th round jeffries had learned much of his trade training with corbett and was now handled by corbetts old manager william brady corbett who had been put on the back burner during fitzsimmons reign wasted no time in suggesting a title fight between his old sparring partner and himself brady liking corbett and reflecting after a recent poor showing against tom sharkey that his old fighter had little left in the tank at  agreed to the match the fight was set for the seaside arena in coney island new york while jeffries went through the motions in training corbett prepared like a spartan for battle he knew with his speed he could box rings around his larger and stronger opponent but he was giving up size strength almost  lb in weight and a sevenyear age difference the key was stamina and the ability to last the round fight limit the early rounds saw corbett moving quickly while big jeff attempted body shots however jeffries could not lay a glove on the dancing master round after round corbett had his way darting in to land punches then dancing away to avoid retaliation by the th round jeffries corner was in a panic manager brady dismissed trainer tommy ryan from the corner and took charge himself with the simple but direct order knock him out or lose your title corbett only had to stay upright for the last five rounds to be heavyweight champion once again jeffries stalked corbett around the ring looking for an opening corbett danced away from any threat through the nd round midway through the rd round corbett leaned back to avoid a jeffries blow bounced off the ropes and was put on the canvas by a short right hand he was counted out corbett found himself embraced by the public after this gallant effort the adoration was shortlived as his next fight a fiveround knockout over kid mccoy was widely believed to be a fix corbett managed to contest for the heavyweight title one last time when he met jeffries for a second match in san francisco in  now  reflexes slowing corbett survived a withering body blow in the second round and used every trick he knew to hang on until being knocked out in the tenth professional boxing recordedit  wins  knockouts  defeats  knockouts  draws  no contests res record opponent type rd time date location notes loss  james j jeffries tko    mechanics pavilion san francisco california for world heavyweight title win  kid mccoy ko    madison square garden new york new york loss  james j jeffries ko     seaside ac coney island new york for world heavyweight title loss  tom sharkey dq    lenox ac new york new york loss  bob fitzsimmons ko   the race track arena carson city nevada lost world heavyweight title draw  tom sharkey pts    mechanics pavilion san francisco california win  charley mitchell ko   duvall athletic club jacksonville florida retained world heavyweight title win  john l sullivan ko    olympic club new orleans louisiana won world heavyweight title win  ed kinney pts   milwaukee wisconsin nc  peter jackson nc   california ac san francisco california win  dominick mccaffrey tko    fifth avenue casino brooklyn new york win  jake kilrain pts   southern ac new orleans louisiana draw  dave campbell pts   mechanics pavilion portland oregon win  australian billy smith pts   portland oregon win  australian billy smith pts   portland oregon win  joe choynski ko   benicia harbor california nc  joe choynski nc   fairfax california win  william miller pts   san francisco california draw  duncan mcdonald pts   opera house salt lake city utah win  frank smith dq   pavilion salt lake city utah life after boxingedit james j corbett applying acting makeup following his retirement from boxing corbett returned to acting appearing in lowbudget films and giving talks about pugilism he also performed a minstrel show in blackface in skits with cornelius j obrien he authored his autobiography under the title the roar of the crowd the story was serialized by the saturday evening post in six weekly installments during octobernovember  the following year gp putnams sons published it in book form marketing it as the true tale of the rise and fall of a champion in  the story was made into a hollywood motion picture titled gentleman jim starring errol flynn as corbett from  until his death corbett lived at  corbett road in a threestory home in the bayside neighborhood of the borough of queens in new york city in  he had a friendly sparring match with the future champion gene tunney an admirer of corbetts scientific style tunney was amazed at the ability of corbett to spar even at the age of about  even claiming corbett had better defense than benny leonard on his passing in  corbett was interred in the cypress hills cemetery in brooklyn new york on its creation he was elected posthumously to the international boxing hall of fame corbetts brother joe corbett was a major league baseball pitcher corbett was married to mary olive morris higgins from  to  after their divorce he married the actress jessie taylor also known by her stage name vera she survived corbett by more than a quarter century living in their home at  corbett road in bayside new york corbetts greatgreatgreatnephew dan corbett was a professional heavyweight boxer from san antonio texas who won the united states boxing federation and international boxing organization intercontinental heavyweight titles before retiring in  the actor james davidson played corbett in the episode the fight san francisco never forgot of the syndicated western television series death valley days hosted by ronald w reagan in the story line walter watson john mcliam becomes boxing instructor at the olympic club in san francisco in this capacity he fights off a local bully and begins training corbett to face him in a match vital to the future of watson and the club corbett had a record of  wins with  by knockout  losses  draws  no contests and  no decisions